{"id":1126677874,"question_id":3252,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"5 months, 3 weeks","timestamp":1703343774,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"139 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1126677874/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Count the Number of Incremovable Subarrays I","memory":"45.3 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int incremovableSubarrayCount(int[] nums) {\n        int len = nums.length;\n        \n        int cnt= 0 ;\n        for(int win=0; win<nums.length; win++){\n            \n            for(int st=0; st+win<len; st++){\n                int ed = st+win;\n                \n                List<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();\n            \n                \n                for(int i=0; i<len; i++){\n                    \n                    if(i<st || i>ed){\n                      \n                        list.add(nums[i]);\n                    }\n                }\n                \n                \n                if(isAsc(list)){\n                      // System.out.println(list + \" true\");\n                    cnt++;\n                }\n                     // System.out.println(list );\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return cnt;\n        \n        \n    }\n    \n    \n    \n    private boolean isAsc( List<Integer> list){\n        \n        for(int i=0; i<list.size()-1; i++){\n            \n            if(list.get(i)>=list.get(i+1)){\n                return false;\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return true;\n        \n        \n    }\n    \n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"count-the-number-of-incremovable-subarrays-i","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
